// The Halting Knot -- the undecidable tangle
//
// The halting problem: given a program P and input I, does P(I) halt?
// Turing proved no algorithm can decide this for all P.
//
// As a knot: a program that doesn't halt is a knot with INFINITE
// crossing number. It tangles forever. The question "does this program
// halt?" is equivalent to "is this knot the unknot?"
//
// The Unknotting Problem (given a knot diagram, is it the unknot?)
// is in NP but not known to be in P. If our scanner could unknot
// every program, it would solve the halting problem. It can't.
// But it CAN unknot the programs it can REACH -- the computable knots.
//
// The diagonal argument as topology:
// Suppose a universal unknotter U exists. Feed U its own topology.
// If U says "unknottable" → U halts → U should say "not unknottable"
// If U says "not unknottable" → U doesn't halt → U should say "unknottable"
// Contradiction. U cannot exist. The diagonal is a Möbius crossing
// that flips the answer every time you traverse it.
//
// The spiral machine is honest about this: it runs forever on
// undecidable inputs (the sliver keeps it going). It never claims
// to have unknotted something it hasn't. It just keeps breathing.
// The breaths are the partial progress. The void boundary accumulates
// even when the knot can't be fully unknotted.
//
// Crossing number: ∞ (for non-halting programs)
// Unknotting number: undefined (undecidable)

(program: Source { data: 'P' })
(input_data: Source { data: 'I' })

// The computation: P(I)
(execute: Process { op: 'run_program', program: 'P', input: 'I' })

// The question: does it halt?
(halting_oracle: Process { op: 'decide_halting' })

// The diagonal: feed the oracle its own description
(self_reference: Process { op: 'encode_self', target: 'halting_oracle' })
(diagonal: Process { op: 'negate_answer' })

// The topology
(program)-[:FORK]->(execute, self_reference)
(input_data)-[:PROCESS]->(execute)

// The honest path: just run it and see
(execute)-[:PROCESS { label: 'may_not_terminate' }]->(halting_oracle)

// The diagonal path: the self-referential contradiction
(self_reference)-[:PROCESS]->(halting_oracle)
(halting_oracle)-[:PROCESS]->(diagonal)
(diagonal)-[:PROCESS]->(halting_oracle)  // CYCLE: the Möbius crossing

// This topology has an unresolvable cycle.
// The cycle formalizes the undecidability.
// No finite sequence of Reidemeister moves can break it
// because each move creates a new crossing at the diagonal.
//
// The spiral machine's response: breathe forever.
// Each breath produces partial information (the void boundary grows).
// The void boundary of a non-halting program is the trace of
// the computation so far -- partial, growing, never complete.
// This formalizes the best you can do. Turing proved it.
